RIJX (http://rijx.com) aims to provide reliable Los Angeles VPS hosting at low prices with combination of great network &amp; stability.
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Hardware&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
All nodes run on server grade HP hardware with enterprise Seagate SAS drives and high end RAID Cards in RAID10 arrays with Flash caching for data protection in case of power loss. Want to know the exact configuration of the node you are on? Submit a ticket and we'll be glad to give you full detailed information!
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Custom VPS Panel&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
We have spent a lot of time building our custom panel with clients in mind. View your assigned resources and current CPU, Memory, vSwap &amp; Bandwidth activity. In addition, you can see the current status of your VPS and uptime / node that you are on.We provide temporary console access using noVNC or java console to regain access to your VM. Furthermore, you can reinstall and take snapshot of your VM which is hosted off site. &lt;a href="http://rijx.com/features.html"&gt;Read More&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Since our launch on LET/LEB we have encountered several bugs reported by our clients which of all have been fixed, we continue to make improvement to our backend and slowly make progress through addition of new features. Bandwidth unlike majority of here reset on the 1st, we reset on your due date every month for both annual and monthly plans. One login for billing and control panel. We have developed Auto Null in cases of DDoS for both outbound and inbound with emails being sent to clients. We are looking to implement IPv6 Subnets, DNS Hosting and other suggested features in the near future. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
All monthly plans include one free snapshot for your VPS, new orders for yearly plans as of now are excluded from this feature. It can be added on for $5/year by submitting ticket to sales.
